    <item>
      <title>LitJour</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/litjour/litjour/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>faultypointer@proton.me (faultypointer)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/litjour/litjour/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;litjour&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  LitJour&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#litjour&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;LitJour, short for Literature Journal, is a platform for book lovers to share their thoughts and connect with others. Write daily journals about the books you&amp;rsquo;re reading, post reviews of books you&amp;rsquo;ve finished, and discover what others are enjoying. With a focus on community and open sharing, LitJour makes it easy to explore, reflect, and discuss your literary journey.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>PngMe</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/pngme/pngme/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>faultypointer@proton.me (faultypointer)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/pngme/pngme/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A program that encodes a message into a png image. (also decodes)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;png-specification&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  PNG Specification&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#png-specification&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;chunk-types&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Chunk Types&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#chunk-types&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Chunk type codes are assigned so that a decoder can determine some properties of a chunk even when it does not recognize the type code. These rules are intended to allow safe, flexible extension of the PNG format, by allowing a decoder to decide what to do when it encounters an unknown chunk. The naming rules are not normally of interest when the decoder does recognize the chunk&amp;rsquo;s type.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TONICA</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/tonica/tonica/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>faultypointer@proton.me (faultypointer)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/tonica/tonica/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;tonica&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  TONICA&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#tonica&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A chess UCI Engine written in Zig.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;contents&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Contents&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#contents&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#about-the-engine&#34;&gt;About The Engine&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#board-representation&#34;&gt;Board Representation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#move-generation&#34;&gt;Move Generation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#searching&#34;&gt;Searching&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#evaluation&#34;&gt;Evaluation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#communication&#34;&gt;Communication&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#building&#34;&gt;Building&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#references&#34;&gt;References&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;about-the-engine&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  About The Engine&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#about-the-engine&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tonica is a UCI (it only supports very few uci commands currently) chess Engine written in zig. I don&amp;rsquo;t know what&amp;rsquo;s its elo&#xA;is as I have not tested it that much. Although it can beat me fairly easily. It is still very simple and there are a lot of features&#xA;to add and some of them are very necessary stuff like time management.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Zhip-8</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/zhip8/zhip8/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>faultypointer@proton.me (faultypointer)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/projects/zhip8/zhip8/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Chip-8 emulator in zig&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-chip8&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  What is chip8?&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#what-is-chip8&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Chip-8 is a simple, interpreted, programming language which was first used on some do-it-yourself computer systems in the late 1970s and early 1980s. The COSMAC VIP, DREAM 6800, and ETI 660 computers are a few examples. These computers typically were designed to use a television as a display, had between 1 and 4K of RAM, and used a 16-key hexadecimal keypad for input. The interpreter took up only 512 bytes of memory, and programs, which were entered into the computer in hexadecimal, were even smaller.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
